414.title: Pierre Thierry
414.clickbait: Automatically generated page for Pierre Thierry
414.text:
[summary: I'm a bayesian rationalist disciple of Christ.]

I have been a science-lover pretty much as long as I have human memories, but for most of my life I was a Traditional Rationalist like my father, openly cultivating the virtue of being able to be proven wrong, albeit actually waiting for a mountain of evidence to eventually do so (and sometimes doing it).

I intend to write an answer to [How to Convince Me That 2 + 2 = 3](http://lesswrong.com/lw/jr/how_to_convince_me_that_2_2_3/)'s question "*what situation would convince you of the truth of Islam?*", being a non-numerophobe Christian who knows Bayes's theorem (and actually reads E.T. Jayneâ€¦).
